Comment: im_a_oncer said "So a while ago I grew out of my best friend. For 5 months she didn't say a word to me. When we made plans she wouldn't show up. She would act completely different around me. When we would hang out and she would actually bother to show up we would spend what felt like forever doing "remember when's" instead of making new memories. For a long time I thought it was my fault, that I was doing something wrong. So I got very depressed. And then one day I realized something. That if I would stop putting an effort into that friendship their wouldn't be any friendship because it was my effort alone. So I let go. I stopped trying to hold onto something that was and no longer is. And slowly I started to become happier. And I honestly think that I am better off without her. Late night bike riding and coming in contact with a moving vehicle at 25mph nearly head on slamming my right shoulder, ripping off the driver side car mirror,  flying off my bike doing a 720 spin in the air, landing on my back while the back of my helmet plants the pavement at full speed. I got back up immediately with my body bruised, startled and shaken up. Lost my vision for 5 minutes, gained consciousness, then lost it again for another 2. That day wasn't fun at all. Took the ambulance to the hospital, saw some doctors, took some x-rays and walked out smiling without a single broken bone in my body. Just a laceration on my right knee and contusion to my right shoulder. I'm blessed to be alive and thankful for everything before me. Things could have been worse but still happy to hold everything God has given me. God is Good all the time. The moral of the story is anything can happen at a moment's notice.
